{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860241710,"sessionID":"ses_2867b8506ffePv44b58CTziFqY","part":{"id":"prt_d7984cebd0019fXwECLsqMA90l","messageID":"msg_d7984b90f001fG7Z56hySjsqnW","sessionID":"ses_2867b8506ffePv44b58CTziFqY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5e8028f5cad347a7a50ae787","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-019\n4: - **Module**: cmd\n5: - **Language**: Go\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: AgentCube provides four CLI binary entry points for its Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform. Each binary serves a distinct role in the system architecture, communicating via the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group using the generated client-go library.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Binary Overview\n16: \n17: | Binary | Purpose | Port | Dependencies |\n18: |--------|---------|------|--------------|\n19: | `agentd` | K8s Reconciler Controller | N/A | K8s API Server, etcd |\n20: | `picod` | Code Execution Daemon | 8080 (configurable) | Local filesystem |\n21: | `router` | HTTP Session Router | 8080 | Redis/Valkey, WorkloadManager |\n22: | `workload-manager` | Sandbox Lifecycle Manager | 8080 | K8s API Server, Redis/Valkey |\n23: \n24: ### 1.3 Component Structure\n25: \n26: ```\n27: cmd/\n28: ├── agentd/\n29: │   ├── main.go                      # Controller entry point\n30: │   └── ...\n31: ├── picod/\n32: │   ├── main.go                      # Code execution daemon entry\n33: │   └── ...\n34: ├── router/\n35: │   ├── main.go                      # Router entry point\n36: │   └── ...\n37: └── workload-manager/\n38:     ├── main.go                      # Workload manager entry point\n39:     └── ...\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ### 1.4 Architecture Diagram\n43: \n44: ```\n45: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n46: │                              AgentCube System                                │\n47: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n48: │                                                                             │\n49: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n50: │  │                        agentd (Controller)                           │   │\n51: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n52: │  │  │  Watches: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CRDs                 │  │   │\n53: │  │  │  Creates: Pods, Services, ConfigMaps                          │  │   │\n54: │  │  │  Status Updates: AgentRuntimeStatus, CodeInterpreterStatus    │  │   │\n55: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n56: │  └──────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n57: │                                 │                                             │\n58: │                                 │ K8s API                                     │\n59: │                                 ▼                                             │\n60: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n61: │  │                    Kubernetes API Server                             │   │\n62: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐   │   │\n63: │  │  │ AgentRuntime    │  │ CodeInterpreter │  │ Pod/Service/Config │   │   │\n64: │  │  │ (CRD)          │  │ (CRD)           │  │ (Native resources)│   │   │\n65: │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘   │   │\n66: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n67: │                                    │                                         │\n68: ├────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤\n69: │                                    │                                         │\n70: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n71: │  │                    workload-manager                                 │   │\n72: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n73: │  │  │ HTTP API    │  │ Sandbox CRUD │  │ Session Lifecycle       │   │   │\n74: │  │  │ (Gin)       │  │              │  │                         │   │   │\n75: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n76: │  └──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n77: │                                 │                                           │\n78: │                                 │ Session events                            │\n79: │                                 ▼                                           │\n80: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n81: │  │                    Redis/Valkey (Session Store)                     │   │\n82: │  │  - Session data (session-routing)                                   │   │\n83: │  │  - Sandbox state                                                    │   │\n84: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n85: │                                    │                                         │\n86: │                                    │ Proxy routing                           │\n87: │                                    ▼                                         │\n88: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n89: │  │                         router                                      │   │\n90: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n91: │  │  │ Session     │  │ Auth/JWT    │  │ Backend Health Check    │   │   │\n92: │  │  │ Routing     │  │ Middleware  │  │                          │   │   │\n93: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n94: │  └──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n95: │                                 │                                           │\n96: │                                 │ HTTP Requests                             │\n97: │                                 ▼                                           │\n98: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n99: │  │                      Sandbox Pods                                   │   │\n100: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n101: │  │  │ Agent        │  │ Code         │  │ Services                 │   │   │\n102: │  │  │ Container    │  │ Interpreter  │  │ (NodePort/ClusterIP)    │   │   │\n103: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n104: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n105: │                                    │                                         │\n106: │                                    │ Optional                                │\n107: │                                    ▼                                         │\n108: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n109: │  │                         picod                                       │   │\n110: │  │  - Code execution daemon inside sandbox pods                       │   │\n111: │  │  - File operations, execution                                       │   │\n112: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n113: │                                                                             │\n114: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ### 1.5 Data Flow\n118: \n119: ```\n120:                                     ┌─────────────────┐\n121:                                     │   Client Request│\n122:                                     └────────┬────────┘\n123:                                              │\n124:                                              ▼\n125:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n126:                                │      router             │\n127:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n128:                                │  │ Auth Middleware   │  │\n129:                                │  │ JWT/Token Review  │  │\n130:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n131:                                │            │            │\n132:                                │            ▼            │\n133:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n134:                                │  │ Session Manager   │  │\n135:                                │  │ → Redis lookup    │  │\n136:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n137:                                │            │            │\n138:                                │            ▼            │\n139:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n140:                                │  │ Backend Selector  │  │\n141:                                │  │ → WorkloadManager │  │\n142:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n143:                                └───────────┬─────────────┘\n144:                                            │\n145:                                            ▼\n146:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n147:                                │  workload-manager      │\n148:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n149:                                │  │ API Handlers      │  │\n150:                                │  │ GET/POST/DELETE   │  │\n151:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n152:                                │            │            │\n153:                                │            ▼            │\n154:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n155:                                │  │ Client-go         │  │\n156:                                │  │ → K8s API         │  │\n157:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n158:                                └───────────┬─────────────┘\n159:                                            │\n160:                                            ▼\n161:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n162:                                │  Kubernetes API Server  │\n163:                                │  - Create AgentRuntime │\n164:                                │  - Create Pod/Service  │\n165:                                └───────────┬─────────────┘\n166:                                            │\n167:                                            ▼\n168:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n169:                                │      agentd             │\n170:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n171:                                │  │ Controller        │  │\n172:                                │  │ → Reconcile loop  │  │\n173:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n174:                                └─────────────────────────┘\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ## 2. Binary Specifications\n178: \n179: ### 2.1 agentd — Kubernetes Controller\n180: \n181: **Entry Point**: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n182: \n183: The agentd binary runs as a Kubernetes controller using controller-runtime. It watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources and ensures the desired runtime state matches the actual cluster state.\n184: \n185: #### Command-Line Flags\n186: \n187: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n188: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n189: | `--metrics-bind-address` | string | \"0\" | Metrics server bind address (0 = disabled) |\n190: | `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | \"0\" | Health probe bind address |\n191: | `--leader-elect` | bool | false | Enable leader election |\n192: | `--leader-elect-lease-duration` | duration | 15s | Leader election lease duration |\n193: | `--leader-elect-renew-deadline` | duration | 10s | Leader election renew deadline |\n194: | `--leader-elect-retry-period` | duration | 5s | Leader election retry period |\n195: \n196: #### Configuration\n197: \n198: ```go\n199: type AgentdConfig struct {\n200:     // Metrics server configuration\n201:     MetricsBindAddress string\n202:     \n203:     // Health probe configuration  \n204:     HealthProbeBindAddress string\n205:     \n206:     // Leader election\n207:     LeaderElect        bool\n208:     LeaseDuration      time.Duration\n209:     RenewDeadline      time.Duration\n210:     RetryPeriod        time.Duration\n211:     \n212:     // Namespace to watch (empty = all namespaces)\n213:     WatchNamespace     string\n214:     \n215:     // Sync period for full reconciliation\n216:     SyncPeriod         time.Duration\n217:     \n218:     // Max concurrent reconciles\n219:     MaxConcurrentReconciles int\n220: }\n221: ```\n222: \n223: #### Dependencies\n224: \n225: - `pkg/agentd/` — Controller implementation\n226: - `pkg/client/informers/` — Generated informers\n227: - `pkg/client/listers/` — Generated listers\n228: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` — API types\n229: \n230: ### 2.2 picod — Code Execution Daemon\n231: \n232: **Entry Point**: `cmd/picod/main.go`\n233: \n234: The picod binary runs inside sandbox pods as a code execution daemon, providing file operations and code execution capabilities.\n235: \n236: #### Command-Line Flags\n237: \n238: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n239: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n240: | `--port` | int | 8080 | Server listen port |\n241: | `--workspace` | string | \"\" | Root directory for file operations (default: cwd) |\n242: | `--auth-mode` | string | \"picod\" | Authentication mode: picod, none |\n243: | `--session-timeout` | duration | 15m | Session timeout |\n244: | `--max-session-duration` | duration | 8h | Maximum session duration |\n245: \n246: #### Configuration\n247: \n248: ```go\n249: type PicoDConfig struct {\n250:     Port              int\n251:     Workspace         string\n252:     AuthMode          string\n253:     SessionTimeout    time.Duration\n254:     MaxSessionDuration time.Duration\n255: }\n256: ```\n257: \n258: #### API Endpoints\n259: \n260: | Method | Path | Description |\n261: |--------|------|-------------|\n262: | GET | `/health` | Health check |\n263: | POST | `/execute` | Execute code |\n264: | GET | `/files/*path` | Read file |\n265: | PUT | `/files/*path` | Write file |\n266: | DELETE | `/files/*path` | Delete file |\n267: \n268: #### Dependencies\n269: \n270: - `pkg/picod/` — Server implementation\n271: \n272: ### 2.3 router — HTTP Session Router\n273: \n274: **Entry Point**: `cmd/router/main.go`\n275: \n276: The router binary provides HTTP routing with session management, authentication, and proxy capabilities. It routes incoming requests to the appropriate sandbox backend based on session affinity.\n277: \n278: #### Command-Line Flags\n279: \n280: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n281: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n282: | `--listen-address` | string | \":8080\" | Server listen address |\n283: | `--workload-manager-url` | string | \"\" | WorkloadManager backend URL (required) |\n284: | `--backend-timeout` | duration | 30s | Backend request timeout |\n285: | `--idle-timeout` | duration | 60s | Idle connection timeout |\n286: | `--health-check-interval` | duration | 10s | Health check interval |\n287: | `--health-check-timeout` | duration | 5s | Health check timeout |\n288: | `--max-conns-per-backend` | int | 100 | Max connections per backend |\n289: | `--rate-limit-enabled` | bool | false | Enable rate limiting |\n290: | `--rate-limit-rps` | int | 10 | Rate limit RPS |\n291: | `--auth-enabled` | bool | false | Enable authentication |\n292: | `--auth-token` | string | \"\" | Bearer token for auth |\n293: | `--session-enabled` | bool | false | Enable session management |\n294: | `--session-timeout` | duration | 30m | Session timeout |\n295: | `--session-cookie-name` | string | \"AGENTSESSIONID\" | Session cookie name |\n296: | `--jwt-enabled` | bool | false | Enable JWT authentication |\n297: | `--jwt-secret` | string | \"\" | JWT secret for HS256 |\n298: | `--jwt-private-key-path` | string | \"\" | Path to RS256 private key |\n299: | `--jwt-public-key-path` | string | \"\" | Path to RS256 public key |\n300: \n301: #### Configuration\n302: \n303: ```go\n304: type RouterConfig struct {\n305:     ListenAddress       string\n306:     WorkloadManagerURL string\n307:     \n308:     // Backend\n309:     BackendTimeout      time.Duration\n310:     IdleTimeout         time.Duration\n311:     HealthCheckInterval time.Duration\n312:     HealthCheckTimeout  time.Duration\n313:     MaxConnsPerBackend  int\n314:     \n315:     // Rate limiting\n316:     RateLimitEnabled    bool\n317:     RateLimitRPS        int\n318:     \n319:     // Auth\n320:     AuthEnabled         bool\n321:     AuthToken           string\n322:     \n323:     // Session management\n324:     SessionEnabled         bool\n325:     SessionTimeout         time.Duration\n326:     SessionCookieName      string\n327:     SessionMaxActive       int\n328:     SessionCookieSecure    bool\n329:     SessionCookieHTTPOnly  bool\n330:     SessionCookieDomain    string\n331:     SessionCleanupInterval time.Duration\n332:     \n333:     // JWT\n334:     JWTEnabled           bool\n335:     JWTAlgorithm         string\n336:     JWTSecret            string\n337:     JWTPrivateKeyPath    string\n338:     JWTPublicKeyPath     string\n339:     JWTIssuer            string\n340:     JWTAudience          []string\n341:     JWTExpiration        time.Duration\n342:     JWTRefreshExpiration time.Duration\n343:     JWTClockSkew         time.Duration\n344:     JWTAllowQueryParam   bool\n345: }\n346: ```\n347: \n348: #### Dependencies\n349: \n350: - `pkg/router/` — Router implementation\n351: - `pkg/store/` — Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n352: - `pkg/client/clientset/` — Generated client-go\n353: \n354: ### 2.4 workload-manager — Sandbox Lifecycle Manager\n355: \n356: **Entry Point**: `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n357: \n358: The workload-manager binary provides REST APIs for sandbox lifecycle management. It creates and manages AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes.\n359: \n360: #### Command-Line Flags\n361: \n362: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n363: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n364: | `--listen-address` | string | \":8080\" | Server listen address |\n365: | `--store-type` | string | \"redis\" | Store type: redis, valkey |\n366: | `--store-address` | string | \"localhost:6379\" | Store address |\n367: | `--store-password` | string | \"\" | Store password |\n368: | `--store-db` | int | 0 | Store database number |\n369: | `--namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default Kubernetes namespace |\n370: | `--session-timeout` | duration | 15m | Default session timeout |\n371: | `--max-session-duration` | duration | 8h | Default max session duration |\n372: | `--gc-interval` | duration | 5m | Garbage collection interval |\n373: | `--gc-worker-count` | int | 5 | GC worker count |\n374: \n375: #### Configuration\n376: \n377: ```go\n378: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n379:     // Server\n380:     ListenAddress string\n381:     \n382:     // Store (Redis/Valkey)\n383:     StoreType    string\n384:     StoreAddress string\n385:     StorePassword string\n386:     StoreDB      int\n387:     \n388:     // Kubernetes\n389:     Namespace string\n390:     \n391:     // Session defaults\n392:     SessionTimeout       time.Duration\n393:     MaxSessionDuration   time.Duration\n394:     \n395:     // Garbage collection\n396:     GCInterval     time.Duration\n397:     GCWorkerCount  int\n398:     \n399:     // Webhook configuration (optional)\n400:     Webhooks []WebhookConfig\n401: }\n402: \n403: type WebhookConfig struct {\n404:     URL        string\n405:     Timeout    int\n406:     RetryCount int\n407: }\n408: ```\n409: \n410: #### API Endpoints\n411: \n412: | Method | Path | Description |\n413: |--------|------|-------------|\n414: | GET | `/health` | Health check |\n415: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | Create sandbox |\n416: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | List sandboxes |\n417: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}` | Get sandbox |\n418: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}` | Delete sandbox |\n419: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | List AgentRuntimes |\n420: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | Create AgentRuntime |\n421: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get AgentRuntime |\n422: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n423: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List CodeInterpreters |\n424: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n425: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n426: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n427: \n428: #### Dependencies\n429: \n430: - `pkg/workloadmanager/` — Manager implementation\n431: - `pkg/store/` — Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n432: - `pkg/client/clientset/` — Generated client-go\n433: \n434: ## 3. API Contracts\n435: \n436: ### 3.1 AgentRuntime (CRD)\n437: \n438: **API Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`  \n439: **Version**: `v1alpha1`  \n440: **Plural**: `agentruntimes`  \n441: **Short Name**: `ar`\n442: \n443: ```yaml\n444: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n445: kind: AgentRuntime\n446: metadata:\n447:   name: my-agent\n448:   namespace: default\n449: spec:\n450:   maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n451:   sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n452:   targetPorts:\n453:     - port: 8080\n454:       protocol: HTTP\n455:       name: http\n456:   podTemplate:\n457:     spec:\n458:       containers:\n459:         - name: agent\n460:           image: my-agent:latest\n461:           resources:\n462:             limits:\n463:               cpu: \"1\"\n464:               memory: \"1Gi\"\n465: status:\n466:   phase: Running\n467:   endpoint: \"http://my-agent.default.sandbox.example.com\"\n468:   conditions:\n469:     - type: Ready\n470:       status: \"True\"\n471:       lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ### 3.2 CodeInterpreter (CRD)\n475: \n476: **API Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`  \n477: **Version**: `v1alpha1`  \n478: **Plural**: `codeinterpreters`  \n479: **Short Name**: `ci`\n480: \n481: ```yaml\n482: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n483: kind: CodeInterpreter\n484: metadata:\n485:   name: my-interpreter\n486:   namespace: default\n487: spec:\n488:   authMode: picod\n489:   maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n490:   sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n491:   template:\n492:     image: python:3.11\n493:     command: [\"python\", \"-m\", \"picod\"]\n494:   warmPoolSize: 0\n495: status:\n496:   phase: Running\n497:   endpoint: \"http://my-interpreter.default.sandbox.example.com\"\n498:   ready: true\n499: ```\n500: \n501: ### 3.3 Client-Go Library Usage\n502: \n503: ```go\n504: import (\n505:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n506:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned\"\n507:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n508: )\n509: \n510: config, _ := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", \"\")\n511: clientset, _ := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n512: \n513: // Create AgentRuntime\n514: arClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\")\n515: agentRuntime := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n516:     // ... spec\n517: }\n518: result, err := arClient.Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n519: \n520: // List CodeInterpreters\n521: ciClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\")\n522: list, err := ciClient.List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n523: ```\n524: \n525: ## 4. Error Handling\n526: \n527: ### 4.1 Error Codes\n528: \n529: | Code | Name | Description |\n530: |------|------|-------------|\n531: | 400 | BadRequest | Invalid request format or parameters |\n532: | 401 | Unauthorized | Authentication failed |\n533: | 403 | Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |\n534: | 404 | NotFound | Resource not found |\n535: | 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists |\n536: | 422 | UnprocessableEntity | Validation failed |\n537: | 429 | TooManyRequests | Rate limit exceeded |\n538: | 500 | InternalServerError | Internal server error |\n539: | 502 | BadGateway | Upstream unavailable |\n540: | 503 | ServiceUnavailable | Service temporarily unavailable |\n541: | 504 | GatewayTimeout | Upstream timeout |\n542: \n543: ### 4.2 Error Response Format\n544: \n545: ```json\n546: {\n547:   \"error\": {\n548:     \"code\": 404,\n549:     \"message\": \"Resource not found\",\n550:     \"details\": {\n551:       \"resource\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n552:       \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n553:       \"namespace\": \"default\"\n554:     }\n555:   }\n556: }\n557: ```\n558: \n559: ### 4.3 Common Errors\n560: \n561: | Error | HTTP Code | Retry | Resolution |\n562: |-------|-----------|-------|------------|\n563: | SandboxNotFound | 404 | No | Check name/namespace |\n564: | DeletionFailed | 500 | Yes | Check K8s cluster state |\n565: | StaleFinalizer | 500 | No | Manual cleanup required |\n566: | OrphanedResource | 500 | Yes | Force delete |\n567: | ResourceNotFound | 404 | No | Resource already deleted |\n568: \n569: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n570: \n571: ### 5.1 Unit Tests\n572: \n573: Each binary should have unit tests for:\n574: - Configuration parsing\n575: - Flag handling\n576: - Error cases\n577: \n578: ```go\n579: // Example: router configuration test\n580: func TestRouterConfig(t *testing.T) {\n581:     tests := []struct {\n582:         name    string\n583:         flags   []string\n584:         wantErr bool\n585:     }{\n586:         {\n587:             name:    \"valid config with required flags\",\n588:             flags:   []string{\"--workload-manager-url\", \"http://localhost:8080\"},\n589:             wantErr: false,\n590:         },\n591:         {\n592:             name:    \"missing required flag\",\n593:             flags:   []string{},\n594:             wantErr: true,\n595:         },\n596:     }\n597:     \n598:     for _, tt := range tests {\n599:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n600:             // Test configuration parsing\n601:         })\n602:     }\n603: }\n604: ```\n605: \n606: ### 5.2 Integration Tests\n607: \n608: - End-to-end binary startup tests\n609: - K8s client integration tests (requires test cluster)\n610: - Store integration tests (requires Redis/Valkey)\n611: \n612: ### 5.3 Build Verification\n613: \n614: ```bash\n615: # Build all binaries\n616: go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n617: go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n618: go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n619: go build -o bin/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n620: \n621: # Verify binaries exist and are executable\n622: ls -la bin/\n623: ```\n624: \n625: ## 6. Dependencies\n626: \n627: ### 6.1 Go Module Dependencies\n628: \n629: ```\n630: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube          # Main module\n631:   ├── k8s.io/api                          # K8s API types\n632:   ├── k8s.io/apimachinery                 # K8s utilities\n633:   ├── k8s.io/client-go                   # K8s client\n634:   ├── k8s.io/klog/v2                     # Logging\n635:   ├── k8s.io/controller-runtime          # Controller framework\n636:   ├── github.com/gin-gonic/gin            # HTTP framework\n637:   ├── github.com/redis/go-redis/v9        # Redis client\n638:   ├── github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go      # Valkey client\n639:   ├── github.com/prometheus/client_golang # Metrics\n640:   └── github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5       # JWT support\n641: ```\n642: \n643: ### 6.2 External Dependencies\n644: \n645: | Component | Requirement | Description |\n646: |-----------|-------------|-------------|\n647: | Kubernetes | ≥1.24 | K8s API server |\n648: | Redis/Valkey | ≥6.0 | Session store |\n649: | Docker | Optional | For building agent images |\n650: \n651: ## 7. Configuration Precedence\n652: \n653: Configuration is loaded in the following order (later overrides earlier):\n654: \n655: 1. Default values (hardcoded)\n656: 2. Environment variables (`AGENTCUBE_*`)\n657: 3. Config file (`/etc/agentcube/config.yaml`)\n658: 4. Command-line flags\n659: \n660: ### 7.1 Environment Variables\n661: \n662: | Variable | Binary | Description |\n663: |----------|--------|-------------|\n664: | `AGENTCUBE_KUBECONFIG` | all | Path to kubeconfig |\n665: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | all | Default namespace |\n666: | `AGENTD_METRICS_ADDR` | agentd | Metrics address |\n667: | `ROUTER_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | router | Backend URL |\n668: | `ROUTER_STORE_ADDRESS` | router | Redis/Valkey address |\n669: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_STORE_ADDRESS` | workload-manager | Store address |\n670: | `PICOD_WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n671: \n672: ### 7.2 Config File Format\n673: \n674: ```yaml\n675: # /etc/agentcube/config.yaml\n676: apiVersion: v1\n677: kind: AgentCubeConfig\n678: metadata:\n679:   name: agentcube\n680: spec:\n681:   namespace: default\n682:   session:\n683:     timeout: 15m\n684:     maxDuration: 8h\n685:   store:\n686:     type: redis\n687:     address: localhost:6379\n688:     password: \"\"\n689:   router:\n690:     listenAddress: \":8080\"\n691:     workloadManagerURL: \"http://localhost:8081\"\n692:   workloadManager:\n693:     listenAddress: \":8081\"\n694: ```\n695: \n696: ## 8. Deployment\n697: \n698: ### 8.1 Docker Images\n699: \n700: Each binary is packaged as a separate Docker image:\n701: \n702: ```dockerfile\n703: # For agentd, router, workload-manager\n704: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n705: WORKDIR /build\n706: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n707: RUN go mod download\n708: COPY . .\n709: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /agentd ./cmd/agentd\n710: \n711: FROM alpine:3.19\n712: RUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n713: COPY --from=builder /agentd /agentd\n714: ENTRYPOINT [\"/agentd\"]\n715: ```\n716: \n717: ### 8.2 Kubernetes Deployment\n718: \n719: The system can be deployed using Helm:\n720: \n721: ```yaml\n722: # values.yaml\n723: agentd:\n724:   enabled: true\n725:   replicas: 1\n726:   \n727: router:\n728:   enabled: true\n729:   replicas: 2\n730:   service:\n731:     type: NodePort\n732:     port: 80\n733:     \n734: workloadManager:\n735:   enabled: true\n736:   replicas: 2\n737:   \n738: picod:\n739:   enabled: true  # Deployed as sidecar in sandbox pods\n740: ```\n\n(End of file - total 740 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-019\n- **Module**: cmd\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nAgentCube provides four CLI binary entry points for its Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform. Each binary serves a distinct role in the system architecture, communicating via the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group using the generated client-go library.\n\n### 1.2 Binary Overview\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Port | Dependencies |\n|--------|---------|------|--------------|\n| `agentd` | K8s Reconciler Controller | N/A | K8s API Server, etcd |\n| `picod` | Code Execution Daemon | 8080 (configurable) | Local filesystem |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775860241694,"end":1775860241707}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860241725,"sessionID":"ses_2867b8506ffePv44b58CTziFqY","part":{"id":"prt_d7984d1e6001Nj4ebOtIdtYgpd","messageID":"msg_d7984b90f001fG7Z56hySjsqnW","sessionID":"ses_2867b8506ffePv44b58CTziFqY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_3828e38c6dc84144a6f93d7e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cli-toolkit/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cli-toolkit/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n4: \n5: ## Package layout (every module path and role)\n6: \n7: | Path | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n10: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n11: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n12: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n13: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n14: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n15: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n16: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n17: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n18: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n19: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n20: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n21: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n22: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` |\n23: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` |\n24: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` |\n25: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n26: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n27: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n28: \n29: **Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):  \n30: `agentcube`, `agentcube.cli`, `agentcube.runtime`, `agentcube.operations`, `agentcube.services`  \n31: *(Note: `agentcube.models` is not listed in `[tool.setuptools] packages` but is imported; packaging may rely on setuptools discovery for subpackages — reconstruct imports from source as above.)*\n32: \n33: ## Console script entry point\n34: \n35: ```toml\n36: [project.scripts]\n37: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n38: ```\n39: \n40: Typer app object: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n41: \n42: ## Typer — root callback\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: def main(\n46:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n47:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n48:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n49:     ),\n50:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n51: ) -> None:\n52:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ## Typer — `pack`\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: def pack(\n59:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n60:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n61:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n62:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n63:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n64:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n65:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n66:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n67:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n68: ) -> None:\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## Typer — `build`\n72: \n73: ```python\n74: def build(\n75:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n76:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n77:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n78:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n79:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n80: ) -> None:\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ## Typer — `publish`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def publish(\n87:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n88:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n89:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n90:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n91:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n92:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n93:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n94:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n95:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n96:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n97:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n98:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n99:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n100: ) -> None:\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ## Typer — `invoke`\n104: \n105: ```python\n106: def invoke(\n107:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n108:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n109:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n110:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n111:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n112: ) -> None:\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ## Typer — `status`\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: def status(\n119:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n120:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n121:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n122: ) -> None:\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ## Helper functions (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n126: \n127: ```python\n128: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None: ...\n129: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None: ...  # prints, typer.Exit(1)\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Runtime classes\n133: \n134: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n135: \n136: ```python\n137: class PackRuntime:\n138:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n139:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n140:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n141:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n142:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n143:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n144:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n145:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n146:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n147:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n148:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n149:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n150:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n151:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n152:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n153:     def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n154:     def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### `BuildRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n158: \n159: ```python\n160: class BuildRuntime:\n161:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n162:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n163:     def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n164:     def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n165:     def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n166:     def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n167:     def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### `PublishRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n171: \n172: ```python\n173: class PublishRuntime:\n174:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n175:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n176:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n177:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n178:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n179:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n180:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n181:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### `InvokeRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n185: \n186: ```python\n187: class InvokeRuntime:\n188:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n189:     def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n190:     def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n191:     async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n192:     async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n193: ```\n194: \n195: **Implementation note:** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if the condition is false, `return response` may raise `UnboundLocalError` (as of extracted source).\n196: \n197: ### `StatusRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: class StatusRuntime:\n201:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n202:     def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n203:     def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n204:     def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ## `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n208: \n209: ```python\n210: class DockerService:\n211:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n212:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n213:     def build_image(\n214:         self,\n215:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n216:         context_path: Path,\n217:         image_name: str,\n218:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n219:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n220:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n221:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n222:     def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n223:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n224:     def push_image(\n225:         self,\n226:         image_name: str,\n227:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n228:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n229:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n230:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n231:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n232:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n233:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ## `MetadataService` (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n237: \n238: ```python\n239: class MetadataService:\n240:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n241:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n242:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n243:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n244:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n245:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n246:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n247: ```\n248: \n249: ## `KubernetesProvider` (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`)\n250: \n251: ```python\n252: class KubernetesProvider:\n253:     def __init__(\n254:         self,\n255:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n256:         verbose: bool = False,\n257:         kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n258:     ) -> None: ...\n259:     def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n260:     def deploy_agent(\n261:         self,\n262:         agent_name: str,\n263:    