{"type":"text","timestamp":1775860264052,"sessionID":"ses_2867b8506ffePv44b58CTziFqY","part":{"id":"prt_d79852a3f001P3xuiNV54cUBSd","messageID":"msg_d79850a9d001Mq3taxZNUISbsr","sessionID":"ses_2867b8506ffePv44b58CTziFqY","type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me create a comprehensive design.md for the CLI pack command (AR-020) in the cli-toolkit directory.","time":{"start":1775860264050,"end":1775860264050}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860359456,"sessionID":"ses_2867b8506ffePv44b58CTziFqY","part":{"id":"prt_d79852c75001PRRSb3K6egmKlR","messageID":"msg_d79850a9d001Mq3taxZNUISbsr","sessionID":"ses_2867b8506ffePv44b58CTziFqY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_eaab3703523d49cdbec4f8bc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Pack Command Design\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-020\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Overview\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the AgentCube agent lifecycle workflow. It validates the workspace structure, loads or creates agent metadata, processes dependencies, optionally generates a Dockerfile, and prepares the workspace for subsequent build and publish steps.\n\n### 1.2 Position in Workflow\n\n```\n┌─────────┐    ┌─────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌─────────┐\n│  pack   │───▶│  build  │───▶│ publish  │───▶│ invoke  │\n└─────────┘    └─────────┘    └──────────┘    └─────────┘\n     │                                                   │\n     └───────────────────▶ status ◀─────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.3 Package Structure\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n| `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` |\n| `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n\n## 2. Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        kubectl-agentcube CLI                            │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                         │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                     agentcube.cli.main                          │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐    │   │\n│  │  │  Typer app  │  │ pack cmd    │  │ _handle_error       │    │   │\n│  │  │             │  │             │  │ version_callback    │    │   │\n│  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘    │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                    │                                    │\n│                                    ▼                                    │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                     agentcube.runtime                           │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │   │\n│  │  │                      PackRuntime                         │    │   │\n│  │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────┐   │    │   │\n│  │  │  │ pack()          │  │ _validate_workspace        │   │    │   │\n│  │  │  │                 │  │ _load_or_create_metadata    │   │    │   │\n│  │  │  │                 │  │ _apply_option_overrides     │   │    │   │\n│  │  │  │                 │  │ _generate_dockerfile        │   │    │   │\n│  │  │  │                 │  │ _process_dependencies       │   │    │   │\n│  │  │  │                 │  │ _update_pack_metadata       │   │    │   │\n│  │  │  │                 │  │ _prepare_output_path       │   │    │   │\n│  │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────┘   │    │   │\n│  │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                    │                                    │\n│              ┌─────────────────────┼─────────────────────┐              │\n│              ▼                     ▼                     ▼              │\n│  ┌───────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐  │\n│  │ MetadataService   │  │  DockerService   │  │  (future services)  │  │\n│  │                   │  │                   │  │                     │  │\n│  │ load_metadata()  │  │ build_image()    │  │                     │  │\n│  │ save_metadata()  │  │ generate_docker()│  │                     │  │\n│  │ validate_workspace│  │                   │  │                     │  │\n│  └───────────────────┘  └───────────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘  │\n│              │                     │                                    │\n│              ▼                     ▼                                    │\n│  ┌───────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────┐                           │\n│  │ agent_metadata   │  │    Dockerfile     │                           │\n│  │     .yaml        │  │                  │                           │\n│  └───────────────────┘  └───────────────────┘                           │\n│                                                                         │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 2.2 Data Flow\n\n```\nUser Input (CLI options)\n         │\n         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────┐\n│   Typer pack()          │\n│   (main.py)             │\n└───────────┬─────────────┘\n            │\n            ▼\n┌─────────────────────────┐\n│   PackRuntime.pack()    │\n│                         │\n│  1. validate_workspace  │\n│  2. load_or_create_meta │\n│  3. apply_option_over   │\n│  4. validate_language   │\n│  5. process_dependencies│\n│  6. generate_dockerfile │\n│  7. prepare_output_path │\n│  8. update_pack_metadata│\n└───────────┬─────────────┘\n            │\n            ▼\n┌─────────────────────────┐\n│   Return Result         │\n│   - agent_name          │\n│   - workspace_path      │\n│   - metadata_path       │\n└─────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## 3. CLI Interface\n\n### 3.1 Console Script Entry Point\n\n```toml\n[project.scripts]\nkubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n```\n\n### 3.2 Typer Root Callback\n\n```python\ndef main(\n    version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n        callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n    ),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 3.3 Pack Command Definition\n\n```python\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### 3.4 Pack Command Options\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `.` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n| `--agent-name` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the agent name |\n| `--language` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Programming language (python, java) |\n| `--entrypoint` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the entrypoint command |\n| `--port` | - | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port to expose in the Dockerfile |\n| `--build-mode` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| `--description` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n| `--output` | - | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for packaged workspace |\n| `--verbose` | - | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n### 3.5 Helper Functions\n\n```python\ndef version_callback(value: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Callback for --version option.\"\"\"\n    \ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Handle errors from subcommands.\"\"\"\n    # Prints error message in red\n    # If verbose, prints full traceback\n    # Raises typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n## 4. Runtime Implementation\n\n### 4.1 PackRuntime Class\n\n**Location**: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n        self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n    \n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Main entry point for packaging.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate workspace exists and contains required files.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load existing metadata or create with defaults.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Apply CLI option overrides to metadata.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate language is supported.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Python workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Java workspace has required files.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Process dependencies based on language.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Process Python requirements.txt.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Java pom.xml.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]:\n        \"\"\"Generate Dockerfile if needed.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Generate Python-specific Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Generate Java-specific Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Save final metadata to workspace.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n        \"\"\"Prepare output directory.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Infer entrypoint if not provided.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 4.2 Pack Flow Algorithm\n\n```python\ndef pack(workspace_path: Path, **options) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    # Step 1: Validate workspace structure\n    _validate_workspace_structure(workspace_path)\n    \n    # Step 2: Load or create metadata\n    metadata = _load_or_create_metadata(workspace_path, options)\n    \n    # Step 3: Apply CLI option overrides\n    metadata = _apply_option_overrides(metadata, options)\n    \n    # Step 4: Validate language compatibility\n    _validate_language_compatibility(workspace_path, metadata)\n    \n    # Step 5: Process dependencies\n    _process_dependencies(workspace_path, metadata)\n    \n    # Step 6: Generate Dockerfile\n    dockerfile_path = _generate_dockerfile(workspace_path, metadata)\n    \n    # Step 7: Prepare output path\n    output_path = _prepare_output_path(workspace_path, options.get('output'))\n    \n    # Step 8: Update and save metadata\n    _update_pack_metadata(output_path, metadata, dockerfile_path)\n    \n    return {\n        'agent_name': metadata.agent_name,\n        'workspace_path': str(output_path),\n        'metadata_path': f'{output_path}/agent_metadata.yaml'\n    }\n```\n\n## 5. Data Models\n\n### 5.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n\n**Location**: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n| `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n| `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n| `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n| `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n| `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n| `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n| `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n| `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n\n**Validators**:\n- `validate_language`: ensures value is in `['python', 'java']` (lowercase)\n- `validate_build_mode`: ensures value is in `['local', 'cloud']` (lowercase)\n- `validate_port`: ensures value is between 1 and 65535\n\n### 5.2 MetadataOptions Dataclass\n\n**Location**: `agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n\n| Field | Type | Default |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n| `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n| `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n\n### 5.3 CLI Options to Metadata Mapping\n\n| CLI Option | Metadata Field | Transformation |\n|------------|----------------|----------------|\n| `--agent-name` | `agent_name` | Direct assignment |\n| `--language` | `language` | Lowercase, validate |\n| `--entrypoint` | `entrypoint` | Direct assignment |\n| `--port` | `port` | Validate range 1-65535 |\n| `--build-mode` | `build_mode` | Lowercase, validate |\n| `--description` | `description` | Direct assignment |\n| `--output` | (output path) | Used for destination |\n\n## 6. Services\n\n### 6.1 MetadataService\n\n**Location**: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n    \n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Load metadata from workspace.\"\"\"\n        # Try agent_metadata.yaml first\n        # Fallback to agent.yaml, then metadata.yaml\n        \n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Save metadata to workspace as agent_metadata.yaml.\"\"\"\n        # Uses yaml.dump with default_flow_style=False, indent=2\n        \n    def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n        \"\"\"Update existing metadata with new values.\"\"\"\n        \n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Validate workspace has required structure.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Python workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n        \n    def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate Java workspace requirements.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 6.2 DockerService\n\n**Location**: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n\n```python\nclass DockerService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n    \n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Check if Docker is available and running.\"\"\"\n        \n    def build_image(\n        self,\n        dockerfile_path: Path,\n        context_path: Path,\n        image_name: str,\n        tag: str = \"latest\",\n        build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Build Docker image from Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n        \n    def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Get information about a Docker image.\"\"\"\n        \n    def push_image(\n        self,\n        image_name: str,\n        registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        username: Optional[str] = None,\n        password: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n        \"\"\"Push image to registry.\"\"\"\n        \n    def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Remove a Docker image.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 6.3 Dockerfile Generation\n\n#### Python Dockerfile Template\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM python:3.11-slim\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n\nCOPY . .\n\nEXPOSE {{port}}\n\nENTRYPOINT [{{entrypoint}}]\n```\n\n#### Java Dockerfile Template\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS builder\n\nWORKDIR /build\n\nCOPY pom.xml .\nRUN mvn dependency:go-offline -B\n\nCOPY src ./src\nRUN mvn package -DskipTests\n\nFROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\nCOPY --from=builder /build/target/*.jar app.jar\n\nEXPOSE {{port}}\n\nENTRYPOINT [{{entrypoint}}]\n```\n\n## 7. Error Handling\n\n### 7.1 Error Types\n\n| Error | Condition | Exit Code |\n|-------|-----------|-----------|\n| `ValueError` | Invalid workspace path | 1 |\n| `ValueError` | Missing required files | 1 |\n| `ValueError` | Invalid language/port | 1 |\n| `FileNotFoundError` | Metadata file not found | 1 |\n| `Exception` | General packaging failure | 1 |\n\n### 7.2 Error Handling Flow\n\n```python\ndef pack_command_callback(**options):\n    workspace = options.get('workspace', '.')\n    verbose = options.get('verbose', False)\n    \n    try:\n        runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n        result = runtime.pack(Path(workspace), **options)\n        \n        # Print success with Rich Progress\n        console.print(f\"[green]Successfully packaged agent: {result['agent_name']}[/green]\")\n        console.print(f\"Workspace: {result['workspace_path']}\")\n        console.print(f\"Metadata: {result['metadata_path']}\")\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        _handle_error(e, \"pack\", verbose)\n```\n\n### 7.3 _handle_error Implementation\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Handle errors from subcommands.\"\"\"\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    \n    if verbose:\n        console.print(traceback.format_exc())\n    \n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n## 8. Dependencies\n\n### 8.1 Python Dependencies\n\n**Project dependencies** (pyproject.toml):\n\n- `typer[all]>=0.9.0` - CLI framework\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` - Data validation\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` - YAML parsing\n- `httpx>=0.24.0` - HTTP client\n- `docker>=6.0.0` - Docker SDK\n- `rich>=13.0.0` - Terminal formatting\n- `packaging>=23.0` - Version parsing\n- `importlib-resources>=6.0.0` - Resource loading\n- `semver>=3.0.0` - Semantic versioning\n\n**Optional dependencies**:\n\n- `k8s`: `kubernetes>=28.0.0` - Kubernetes client\n- `dev`: `pytest`, `pytest-asyncio`, `pytest-cov`, `ruff`, `mypy`\n- `test`: `pytest-mock`, `httpx-mock`\n\n### 8.2 Python Version\n\n```\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n```\n\n## 9. Testing Strategy\n\n### 9.1 Unit Tests\n\n```python\n# test_pack_runtime.py\nimport pytest\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n\nclass TestPackRuntime:\n    def test_validate_workspace_structure_missing(self):\n        \"\"\"Test validation fails for missing workspace.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_validate_workspace_structure_python(self):\n        \"\"\"Test validation passes for valid Python workspace.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_validate_workspace_structure_java(self):\n        \"\"\"Test validation passes for valid Java workspace.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_load_or_create_metadata_new(self):\n        \"\"\"Test creating new metadata with defaults.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_load_or_create_metadata_existing(self):\n        \"\"\"Test loading existing metadata.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_apply_option_overrides(self):\n        \"\"\"Test CLI option overrides applied to metadata.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_generate_python_dockerfile(self):\n        \"\"\"Test Python Dockerfile generation.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_generate_java_dockerfile(self):\n        \"\"\"Test Java Dockerfile generation.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_infer_entrypoint_python(self):\n        \"\"\"Test Python entrypoint inference.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 9.2 Integration Tests\n\n```python\n# test_pack_integration.py\nclass TestPackIntegration:\n    def test_pack_python_agent(self):\n        \"\"\"End-to-end test for Python agent packaging.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_pack_java_agent(self):\n        \"\"\"End-to-end test for Java agent packaging.\"\"\"\n        \n    def test_pack_with_custom_output(self):\n        \"\"\"Test packaging with custom output path.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 9.3 Test Fixtures\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef python_workspace(tmp_path):\n    \"\"\"Create a valid Python workspace.\"\"\"\n    (tmp_path / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\")\n    (tmp_path / \"requirements.txt\").write_text(\"requests>=2.28\")\n    return tmp_path\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef java_workspace(tmp_path):\n    \"\"\"Create a valid Java workspace.\"\"\"\n    (tmp_path / \"pom.xml\").write_text(\"<?xml version='1.0'...>\")\n    return tmp_path\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef pack_runtime():\n    \"\"\"Create PackRuntime instance.\"\"\"\n    return PackRuntime(verbose=True)\n```\n\n## 10. Configuration Precedence\n\nConfiguration is resolved in the following order (later overrides earlier):\n\n1. **Default values** (hardcoded in `MetadataOptions`)\n2. **Metadata file** (`agent_metadata.yaml` / `agent.yaml` / `metadata.yaml`)\n3. **CLI options** (explicit command-line arguments)\n\n### 10.1 Metadata File Priority\n\n```\n1. agent_metadata.yaml  (preferred)\n2. agent.yaml          (fallback)\n3. metadata.yaml       (fallback)\n```\n\n## 11. Usage Examples\n\n### 11.1 Basic Pack\n\n```bash\n# Pack current directory as Python agent\nkubectl-agentcube pack\n\n# Pack specific workspace\nkubectl-agentcube pack --workspace /path/to/agent\n\n# Short flag\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f /path/to/agent\n```\n\n### 11.2 Pack with Options\n\n```bash\n# Pack with custom agent name\nkubectl-agentcube pack --agent-name my-agent\n\n# Pack Java agent\nkubectl-agentcube pack --language java\n\n# Pack with custom entrypoint and port\nkubectl-agentcube pack --entrypoint \"python app.py\" --port 9000\n\n# Pack with custom output path\nkubectl-agentcube pack --output /tmp/packed-agent\n\n# Pack with verbose logging\nkubectl-agentcube pack --verbose\n```\n\n### 11.3 Full Workflow\n\n```bash\n# Step 1: Pack the agent\nkubectl-agentcube pack --workspace ./my-agent --language python\n\n# Step 2: Build the container image\nkubectl-agentcube build --workspace ./my-agent\n\n# Step 3: Publish to Kubernetes\nkubectl-agentcube publish --workspace ./my-agent --provider k8s\n\n# Step 4: Check status\nkubectl-agentcube status --workspace ./my-agent\n\n# Step 5: Invoke the agent\nkubectl-agentcube invoke --workspace ./my-agent --payload '{\"task\": \"hello\"}'\n```\n\n## 12. Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Criterion | Validation |\n|----|-----------|------------|\n| AC001 | Pack validates workspace structure before processing | Unit test: invalid path raises ValueError |\n| AC002 | Pack loads or creates metadata with proper defaults | Integration test: new workspace gets defaults |\n| AC003 | Pack merges CLI option overrides into metadata | Unit test: options override metadata fields |\n| AC004 | Pack generates Dockerfile when needed (Python/Java) | Integration test: Dockerfile created |\n| AC005 | Pack processes dependencies for the target language | Unit test: requirements.txt validated |\n| AC006 | Pack prepares output path and saves metadata | Integration test: metadata saved to output |\n| AC007 | Pack displays success output with Rich formatting | Manual test: visual verification |\n| AC008 | Pack handles errors with proper exit codes and verbose logging | Unit test: verbose mode shows traceback |\n| AC009 | Pack validates language and port values | Unit test: invalid values raise ValidationError |\n| AC010 | Pack infers entrypoint when not provided | Unit test: main.py detected for Python |\n\n## 13. References\n\n- Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n- Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n- Delta spec: `changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md`\n- CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n- Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- Docker service: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n- Python SDK: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- client-go library: `deployment/client-go.md`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cli-toolkit/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cli-toolkit/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cli-toolkit/design.md","time":{"start":1775860359314,"end":1775860359453}}}}
